========================================
IntelliPark - Database Migration Guide
========================================

This project uses PostgreSQL with SQLAlchemy and Alembic for database migrations.

----------------------------------------
1. Prerequisites
----------------------------------------

Make sure you have:

- Python installed (3.9+)
- PostgreSQL installed and running
- pgAdmin (optional)
- Project cloned from GitHub

----------------------------------------
2. Setup Virtual Environment
----------------------------------------

cd IntelliPark

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

----------------------------------------
3. Install Dependencies
----------------------------------------

pip install -r requirements.txt

----------------------------------------
4. Create PostgreSQL Database
----------------------------------------

Using pgAdmin or terminal:

CREATE DATABASE intellipark_db;

----------------------------------------
5. Configure Database Connection
----------------------------------------

Create a file in the project root:

.env

Add:

DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://postgres:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/intellipark_db

Replace PASSWORD with your PostgreSQL password.

----------------------------------------
6. Run Database Migrations
----------------------------------------

Run:

alembic upgrade head

This will:
- create all tables
- apply latest schema
- update alembic_version

----------------------------------------
7. Verify Database
----------------------------------------

Open pgAdmin and check:

intellipark_db → Schemas → public → Tables

Expected tables:

- users
- drivers
- admins
- parking_lots
- parking_levels
- parking_spots
- vehicles
- reservations
- parking_sessions
- payments

----------------------------------------
8. Creating a New Migration
----------------------------------------

When you change database models:

Step 1: Update model files (app/db/models)

Step 2: Generate migration:

alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe your change"

Step 3: Apply migration:

alembic upgrade head

----------------------------------------
9. Check Migration Status
----------------------------------------

See current version:

alembic current

See history:

alembic history

----------------------------------------
10. Important Rules
----------------------------------------

- DO NOT create tables manually in pgAdmin
- ALWAYS use Alembic migrations
- DO NOT modify database directly
- DO NOT commit .env file
- ALWAYS pull latest migrations before running backend

----------------------------------------
11. Reset Database (optional)
----------------------------------------

If needed:

DROP DATABASE intellipark_db;
CREATE DATABASE intellipark_db;

Then run:

alembic upgrade head

----------------------------------------
12. Test Database Connection
----------------------------------------

python test_db.py

Expected output:

Database connection works: 1

----------------------------------------
End of Guide
----------------------------------------
